					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Grumskiz wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I would love to try your emulator and it's debugging capabilities on Linux, since the only way I could get that kinda stuff is with FCEUX in wine and that's a pain, because it crashes often.<br /><br />The problem is, that I can't get your source from gitorious to compile.<br />Apparently I'm missing the emulator_core.h file.<br /><br />I remember that you had emulator libs before for nesicide and I'm wondering if I need those.<br />Though, I couldn't find them on your git project overview anymore.</div>
<br />
<br />There's three repositories on gitorious that you'll need:
<br />
<br />git clone <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://git.gitorious.org/nesicide/nesicide.git">https://git.gitorious.org/nesicide/nesicide.git</a><!-- m -->
<br />git clone <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://git.gitorious.org/nesicide/nesicide-emulator.git">https://git.gitorious.org/nesicide/nesi ... ulator.git</a><!-- m -->
<br />git clone <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://git.gitorious.org/nesicide/nesicide-emulator-lib.git">https://git.gitorious.org/nesicide/nesi ... or-lib.git</a><!-- m -->
<br />
<br />The file emulator_core.h is in the last one, which is where the emulator library is located.
<br />
<br />You'll also want to read the first section of the README in the nesicide repository that lists what other things you'll need.</div>

