					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">cpow wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Not sure what Vaus emulation is...but if you could elaborate?</div>
<br /><img src="http://www.gry-pegasus.xaa.pl/obrazki/arkanoid2.jpeg" alt="Image" />
<br />After the mothership <em>Arkanoid</em> was destroyed, player escaped in a Vaus escape pod and must use its chassis to bounce balls back at bricks. 
<br />
<br /><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arkanoid_Controller" class="postlink"><img src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/c3/Vaus.jpg" alt="Image" /></a>
<br />The Vaus Controller is a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paddle_%28game_controller%29" class="postlink">paddle</a> that controls the Vaus (or the car in <em>Chase H.Q.</em>) more precisely than a Control Pad alone. It contains a potentiometer and an ADC.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

